    </section><section id="fs-id1167066770062" class="summary">
<title>Section Summary</title>
<list id="fs-id1167066974425"><item>The law of conservation of momentum is written <emphasis>p</emphasis><sub>tot</sub> = constant or <emphasis>p</emphasis><sub>tot</sub> = <emphasis>p</emphasis>′<sub>tot</sub> (isolated system), where <emphasis>p</emphasis><sub>tot</sub> is the initial total momentum and <emphasis>p</emphasis>′<sub>tot</sub> is the total momentum some time later.</item>
<item>In an isolated system, the net external force is zero.</item>
<item>Conservation of momentum applies only when the net external force is zero, within the defined system.</item>
</list></section>

<section id="fs-id1167066885693" class="key-equations"><title>Key Equations</title><table id="fs-id1167066869547" class="unnumbered unstyled" summary="The list of Key Equations includes the formulas for the law of conservation of momentum, the conservation of momentum for two objects, and angular momentum.">
<label/>
<tgroup cols="2"><colspec colnum="1" align="left" colname="c1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" align="left" colname="c2"/>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry>law of conservation of momentum</entry>
<entry><emphasis>p</emphasis><sub>tot</sub> = constant, or <emphasis>p</emphasis><sub>tot</sub> = <emphasis>p</emphasis>′<sub>tot</sub></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>conservation of momentum for two objects</entry>
<entry><emphasis> p</emphasis><sub>1</sub> + <emphasis>p</emphasis><sub>2</sub> = constant, or <emphasis>p</emphasis><sub>1</sub> + <emphasis>p</emphasis><sub>2</sub> = <emphasis>p</emphasis>′<sub>1</sub> + <emphasis>p</emphasis>′<sub>2</sub></entry>
