<definition id="fs-id1167067036232"><term>angular momentum</term> <meaning id="fs-id1167066863076">the product of the moment of inertia and angular velocity</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167066851277"><term>isolated system</term> <meaning id="fs-id1167066852861">system in which the net external force is zero</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167066864800"><term>law of conservation of momentum</term> <meaning id="fs-id1167066835423">when the net external force is zero, the total momentum of the system is conserved or constant</meaning></definition>

